title: Google's driverless cars have a problem: other drivers
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › Google's driverless cars have a probl... Google's driverless cars have a problem: other drivers Next Story Prev Story 1 hr ago Read more: The Age 
Despite several accidents involving Google's self driving cars in California, tests will begin in South Australia in November to test driverless technology to suit Australia's driving habits and climate. Last month, as one of Google's self-driving cars approached a crosswalk, it did what it was supposed to do when it slowed to allow a pedestrian to cross, prompting its "safety driver" to apply the brakes.
